	"system": {
		"description": {
			"value": "<p><em>You gently stroke a severed piece of a tentacle or tendril of a giant cephalopod, and it begins to wriggle and writhe in your hand as if alive. Moments later, squirming ebony tentacles spring up from the ground.</em></p><p><strong>Dexterity Save</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>Failure:</strong> [[/damage 3d6 bludgeoning]] damage*, and target is &amp;reference[restrained]. Target rolls again at end of their turns: taking full damage on a failure or taking half damage and ending effect on success.</p></li><li><p><strong>Success:</strong> Half damage, no other effect.</p></li><li><p><strong>Area Hazard:</strong> The area is &amp;reference[difficultterrain]. Targets roll a save when they enter or when they end their turn in the tentacles (but only once per turn).</p></li></ul><p></p><p><strong>*Upcasting:</strong> Increase damage by [[/damage 1d6 bludgeoning]]{1d6} for each spell level above 2nd.</p>",
			"chat": ""
		},
